---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Fin Sanctuary Podcasts"
  description="Browse dedicated Fin Sanctuary podcast pages as episodes are published, with each episode receiving its own page and future notes."
>
  <main>
    <section class="border-b border-primary/10 bg-[linear-gradient(180deg,rgba(1,133,174,0.08),rgba(243,239,238,0.55))] dark:border-white/8 dark:bg-[linear-gradient(180deg,rgba(13,175,188,0.14),rgba(2,6,23,0.95))]">
      <div class="mx-auto grid max-w-6xl gap-8 px-6 py-10 md:py-12 xl:grid-cols-[minmax(0,1fr)_22rem] xl:items-end">
        <div>
          <div class="text-[0.72rem] font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.28em] text-primary/75">Podcast Library</div>
          <h1 class="mt-5 font-bold tracking-tight text-primary">Dedicated pages for every Fin Sanctuary podcast episode.</h1>
          <p class="mt-6 max-w-3xl text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-200">
            The podcast section is now part of the site structure, so every future episode can live on its own page with embedded audio, notes, and related links.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-[2rem] border border-primary/10 bg-white/80 p-6 shadow-[0_28px_90px_-55px_rgba(1,133,174,0.45)] backdrop-blur dark:border-white/8 dark:bg-slate-900/82">
          <div class="text-[0.68rem] font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.24em] text-primary/75">Ready For</div>
          <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
            <li>Episode-by-episode pages with shareable URLs.</li>
            <li>Future embedded audio players and show notes.</li>
            <li>Cross-linking from newsletters, guides, and media pages.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6 py-10">
      <div class="rounded-[2rem] border border-dashed border-primary/20 bg-white/70 px-7 py-8 text-center text-slate-600 shadow-[0_24px_80px_-60px_rgba(1,133,174,0.35)] dark:border-primary/20 dark:bg-slate-900/75 dark:text-slate-300">
        The podcast section is now live as its own destination. No episodes are published yet, but this page is the starting point for future episode pages once the first Fin Sanctuary podcast is ready to post.
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>
